{{#seo:|description=Learn about AES Encryption in Clomosy Docs. A guide to implementing secure data encryption using the AES algorithm for your mobile apps.}}

To access information such as the company GUID, project GUID, and project name in an account created with a developer account, the following functions can be used.<br>

<h2> Firm_GUID </h2>
<div class="alert alert-ligth border border-3 border-primary-subtle rounded-5 p-4 shadow-sm" role="alert">
function Clomosy.Firm_GUID: String;
</div>
The GUID of the company where the user is located is provided. Educational accounts do not have a company GUID. For this reason, it returns "CLOSTARTER."<br>

<b>Example</b><br>
<pre>
var
  firm_guid : Integer;

{
  firm_guid = Clomosy.Firm_GUID;
  ShowMessage('Company GUID information: '+firm_guid);
}
</pre>

<h2> Project_GUID	 </h2>
<div class="alert alert-ligth border border-3 border-primary-subtle rounded-5 p-4 shadow-sm" role="alert">
function Clomosy.Project_GUID: String;
</div>

The GUID of the project entered by the user is provided.<br>

<b>Example</b><br>
<pre>
var
  project_guid : String;

{
 project_guid = Clomosy.Project_GUID;
 ShowMessage('Project GUID information: '+project_guid);
}
</pre>

<h2> AppProjectName </h2>
<div class="alert alert-ligth border border-3 border-primary-subtle rounded-5 p-4 shadow-sm" role="alert">
function Clomosy.AppProjectName: String;
</div>
Returns the project name.<br>

<b>Example</b><br>
<pre>
var
  project_name : String;
{
  project_name = Clomosy.AppProjectName;
  ShowMessage('Project name information: '+project_name);
}
</pre>

<h2> See Also </h2>
* [[Clomosy_Class#Account_Information | Account Information]]
{{#seo:|description=Get account information like company GUID, project GUID, and project name in Clomosy using Firm_GUID, Project_GUID, and AppProjectName functions.}}

