<h2> SQL </h2>
It is a query language used to interact with the database. This command is used to access, insert, update, or delete data in the database.<br>

<pre>
Query1.SQL.Text = 'SELECT * FROM table_name';
</pre>

<h2> FieldByName </h2>
It is used to access the value of a specific field in a dataset. This command allows you to reach the data in the current record by using the specified field name.<br>
<pre>
Query1.FieldByName('Price').AsString;
</pre>

<h2> ExecSQL </h2>
It is used to execute an SQL command in the database, typically for data manipulation operations such as insertion, update, or deletion. This command applies the effect of the query (for example, adding a record) without returning a result set.<br>
<pre>
JsonQuery1.SQL.Text = 'DELETE FROM Products WHERE ID = :ID';
JsonQuery1.Params.ParamByName('ID').AsInteger = 5; // Set the parameter
JsonQuery1.ExecSQL; // Execute the query
</pre>

