In Clomosy, a sensor is used in the context of mobile application development to detect the orientation of the device. The 'FormOrientationSensorType' property determines which type of sensor the mobile form will use to track the device's orientation.<br>

For example, if the 'FormOrientationSensorType' property is set to "ostTilt," it will track the tilt of the device.<br>

This property allows applications to track the position of the device, enabling operations like screen rotation. This is particularly important for games, map applications, and other mobile applications.<br>

