The TclSearchBox component is typically used to provide the user with the ability to search within a text list. It allows the user to search for a specific term in a list and filter the items that contain that term.<br>

Designed for ease of use and to enhance the efficiency of search operations, the TclSearchBox is intended to be user-friendly. After the user enters text onto the TclSearchBox, the component can be integrated with a TclListView component to display a list of items that match the entered text.<br>

