The <b>TclShareService</b> is typically used after generating or downloading a file (such as a PDF or CSV), or when you want to share text or images with other applications.  
You can add multiple items (files, images, or text) before calling the <code>Share</code> method. Once <code>Share()</code> is executed, the system’s default share interface appears, allowing the user to select how to share the content.<br>


<div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert" data-bs-theme="light">
<b>Note:</b> When using the <b>AddImage</b> property, you must provide a <b>Bitmap</b> instance instead of a file path or URL.
</div>



